Emmanuella and Liam were in the grocery store in a heated fight that might seriously end their relationship. They were hosting a dinner party that night and had to gather ingredients for the dinner. As they entered the grocery store, it had a large variety of organic food. As the walked along the aisle, Emmanuella picked up a few pasta boxes. 

"I guess tonight will be pasta night," Liam said. 
"If you wanted to actually help, I would be fine with something else."
"I try to help, but it never feels like you listen."
"I honestly doubt that you're even trying," Emmanuella responded as she dropped the pasta boxes into the grocery cart. 

She continued on until she found the pasta sauces. She was picking up a vodka sauce jar, when suddenly she said very calmly, "I think we should break up. I've been thinking about it for a long time. I would have brought it up to you earlier if it wasn't for this horribly timed dinner party. I feel like anytime we try to do anything fun together we always end up arguing over the stupidest thing, and I am way past trying to work through it." Without even realizing, Liam nodded his head. 

As they approached the checkout lanes, they saw that checkout lane 2 was the only one open and headed over. As they were checking out, Emmanuella scrutinized the pasta sauce once again. Liam said, "I agree, I think that we should break up." Liam was happy as he felt the possibility open up that they had just gotten through their last fight. 

The cashier ringed them the items up: it came to a total of $30. Emmanuella paid with her credit card. 

Emmanuella said, "I think that we can still hold the dinner party tonight if you don't mind."
"I agree, we can pretend that we haven't broken up." 
"The first one the reveal the information loses the cat."
Liam chuckled. "Of course I'm getting Luna; she's my cat."

Emanuella sighed as she realized the cat would be a whole other thing they would fight over.
